						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is damaged and dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Hēmaḷambi, Phālguṇa, śu. 10,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya-Mahārāya,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1418 February 16 Wednesday</hi> (not verifiable). It records that the king confirmed the exemption, granted formerly to the <hi rend="italic">Pañchālas</hi> in the four <hi rend="italic">Nāḍus</hi> by king <hi rend="bold">Harihara-Mahārāya,</hi> from taxes on marriages, bullocks, buffaloes, carts loaded with paddy, and the like.</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
